description: From Middle English outspreden, equivalent to out- +‎ spread. Cognate with Dutch uitspreiden (“to outspread, stretch, unfold”), Danish udsprede (“to outspread”), Swedish utspridda (“to outspread”).

adjectives.description: outspread (comparative more outspread, superlative most outspread)

examples: She longed to fall into his outspread arms once again.

verbs.description: outspread (third-person singular simple present outspreads, present participle outspreading, simple past and past participle outspread)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To spread out; expand; extend.
